        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 9. — Macroxenodes jahynyi n. sp.: A-E, female holotype; A, left antenna; B, C, detail of sensilla on articles VII and VI of same antenna; D, labrum, only part of cuticular setae shown; E, left palpus of gnathochilarium; F-H, female paratype; F, seta of tarsus II telotarsus of left leg XI; G, telotarsus of same leg;H, seta of prefemur of left leg VI;I, right antennal article VI of male no. 2 of M. bartschi (Chamberlin,1923) (after Nguyen Duy-Jacquemin & Condé 1984).Abbreviations:c, sensillum coeloconicum;E, short and thick sensilla basiconica; s, setiform sensillum. Scale bars: A, E, 50 μm; B-D, F-I, 25 μm." ;
